Q1What is the atom economy of a reaction?
Q2Give the equation used to nd the atom economy of a reaction.
Q3Give two reasons why reactions with high atom economies are
preferred for use in industry over those with low atom economies.
In industry, atom economy isn’t the only factor to consider when choosing
which reaction pathway to use to make a certain product. These factors also
need to be taken into account:
The percentage yield (see page 189) of the reaction affects how much
useful product is made. The higher the yield, the less reactants are
wasted, so the cheaper the reaction.
The rate of the reaction (see page 223) must be fastenough to produce the
amount of product that is required in a sensible amount of time.
If the reaction is reversible (see page 169), the position of equilibrium
must also be considered. The amount of products formed relative to
the amount of reactants depends on the equilibrium position, so it may
be necessary to alter the position of equilibrium to favour the products.
